&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;At Accenture Federal Services, nothing matters more than helping the US federal government make the nation stronger and safer and life better for people. Our 13,000+ people are united in a shared purpose to pursue the limitless potential of technology and ingenuity for clients across defense, national security, public safety, civilian, and military health organizations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Join Accenture Federal Services, a technology company within global Accenture. Recognized as a Glassdoor Top 100 Best Place to Work, we offer a collaborative and caring community where you feel like you belong and are empowered to grow, learn and thrive through hands-on experience, certifications, industry training and more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Join us to drive positive, lasting change that moves missions and the government forward!&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The work:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead cybersecurity compliance for Federal/DoD systems as an Information System Security Officer (ISSO) and Assessment &amp;amp; Authorization (A&amp;amp;A) specialist; manage all phases of the Risk Management Framework (RMF) to achieve and maintain Authority to Operate (ATO).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full RMF lifecycle (Categorize, Select, Implement, Assess, Authorize, Monitor) for assigned systems to ensure security compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and assess NIST SP 800-53 security controls; perform regular vulnerability scans, security control assessments, and risk analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain required security authorization documentation (e.g., System Security Plans, POA&amp;amp;Ms) and track remediation of identified security findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct continuous security monitoring and periodic reviews to sustain the system’s authorized security posture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in information security/assurance (including Federal/DoD RMF A&amp;amp;A)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of RMF (NIST SP 800-37), NIST SP 800-53 controls, and FISMA compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in implementing and assessing security controls, conducting vulnerability assessments and risk analysis, and managing security documentation (SSPs, POA&amp;amp;Ms, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud security (FedRAMP), high-impact or classified systems, and other specialized federal cybersecurity environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with security compliance tools and GRC platforms; experience with automating continuous monitoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DoD 8570/8140 IAM Level II/III baseline certification (e.g., Security+ or equivalent)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced cybersecurity certifications preferred (e.g., CISSP, CAP, CISM)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
